HEADWORD: Zealotry
<hw>Zeal"ot*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The character and
behavior of a zealot; excess of zeal; fanatical devotion to a
cause.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Enthusiasm, visionariness, seems the tendency of the German; zeal,
<qex>zealotry</qex>, of the English; fanaticism, of the French.</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Zealous</ent>⟦br⟧
